Time for our last note of these first
lessons, Middle C.
Hmmâ€¦ this note is below the Staff and there's a line through it...

This is called a Ledger Line and it allows us to put notes outside of the Staff.  This is only line below the staff, but later we will see many lines above the staff when we play higher notes.  This note is particularly hard to play well so take some time to make it sound good.  It takes a lot of practice to perfect your tone so focus on the shape of your mouth and listen for a good tone.
Lets now try exercises with Middle C.
